### Anything else?


https://github.com/angular/angular/blob/main/packages/common/http/src/fetch.ts#L224 
Here is the root cause. 

If i change the implementation like this, it solved.  
```
      body: req.serializeBody(),
```

In XhrBackend, `serializeBody` convert its body to be serialized json string.

https://github.com/angular/angular/blob/254023a03c3aaa26e2d01c02f9b9933b82fd971e/packages/common/http/src/request.ts#L295

### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

core

### Description

let's say we have a simple directive that has a required input property 'color'
```
import { Directive, Input } from '@angular/core';

@Directive({
  selector: '[appHighlightOnHover]',
  standalone: true,
})
export class HighlightOnHoverDirective {
  @Input({ required: true })
  color!: string;
}
```

we want to use it as Host Directives in a component
```
@Component({
  selector: 'app-my-h1',
  standalone: true,
  imports: [CommonModule, HighlightOnHoverDirective],
  templateUrl: './my-h1.component.html',
  styleUrls: ['./my-h1.component.scss'],
  hostDirectives: [
    {
      directive: HighlightOnHoverDirective,
    },
  ],
})
export class MyH1Component {
   
}
```
boom! it forces us to expose it.
![image](https://github.com/angular/angular/assets/8691013/447988f4-3df3-423c-b6e2-33aee44f1654)
but...why? 
and we don't want to expose it, we do set up internally as below
```
export class MyH1Component implements OnInit {
  constructor() {
    inject(HighlightOnHoverDirective).color = 'red'; 
  }

  private highlightOnHoverDir = inject(HighlightOnHoverDirective);
  ngOnInit(): void {
    this.highlightOnHoverDir.color = 'red';
  }
}
```


### Proposed solution

currently, I don't have any idea. Because both are new things. 

